ids to amino acids; H\u2082 provides reductive power.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Iron-sulfur catalysis shown for \u03b1-keto acids (Muchowska et al., 2019; Cody et al., 2000; Huber & W\u00e4chtersh\u00e4user, 2006; Lane & Martin, 2012; White et al., 2015).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_011\",\n      \"name\": \"Aldol condensation of glycine and acetaldehyde to threonine\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_007\", \"mol_003\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_013\", \"mol_014\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Surface\",\n      \"agents\": [\"montmorillonite\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"80\u00b0C\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"montmorillonite\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"Wet-dry cycling\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Glycine and acetaldehyde react by aldol condensation to threonine/allothreonine diastereomers in presence of clay.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Aldol condensation proposed (Fesko, 2016), glycine + aldehydes produce hydroxy amino acids (Koga & Naraoka, 2022); clay mineral catalysis (Kitadai et al., 2015).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_012\",\n      \"name\": \"HCN polymer hydrolysate yielding threonine (HCN oligomer pathway)\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_001\", \"mol_008\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_013\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Surface\",\n      \"agents\": [\"phosphate minerals\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"30\u00b0C\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"phosphate minerals\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"Wet-dry cycling\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"HCN polymerizes under surface conditions; hydrolysis of HCN oligomers yields threonine (with racemic isomers).\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"HCN polymer hydrolysate yields proteinogenic amino acids including threonine (Ruiz-Bermejo et al., 2013).\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"pathways\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"name\": \"Cyanosulfid